#Text=THE PHANTOM BOWMEN
#Text=As Jav leaped toward him
#Text=Carthoris laid his hand upon the hilt of his long-sword .
#Text=The Lotharian halted .

#Text=The great apartment was empty save for the four at the dais , yet as Jav stepped back from the menace of the Heliumite 's threatening attitude the latter found himself surrounded by a score of bowmen .
#Text=From whence had they sprung ?
#Text=Both Carthoris and Thuvia looked their astonishment .
#Text=Now the former 's sword leaped from its scabbard , and at the same instant the bowmen drew back their slim shafts .
#Text=Tario had half raised himself upon one elbow .
#Text=For the first time he saw the full figure of Thuvia , who had been concealed behind the person of Carthoris .
#Text=" Enough ! " cried the jeddak , raising a protesting hand , but at that very instant the sword of the Heliumite cut viciously at its nearest antagonist .
#Text=As the keen edge reached its goal
#Text=Carthoris let the point fall to the floor , as with wide eyes he stepped backward in consternation , throwing the back of his left hand across his brow .
#Text=His steel had cut but empty air -- his antagonist had vanished --
#Text=there were no bowmen in the room !
#Text=" It is evident that these are strangers , " said Tario to Jav .
#Text=" Let us first determine that they knowingly affronted us before we take measures for punishment . "
#Text=Then he turned to Carthoris , but ever his gaze wandered to the perfect lines of Thuvia 's glorious figure , which the harness of a Barsoomian princess accentuated rather than concealed .
#Text=" Who are you , " he asked , " who knows not the etiquette of the court of the last of jeddaks ? "
#Text=" I am Carthoris , Prince of Helium , " replied the Heliumite .
#Text=" And this is Thuvia , Princess of Ptarth .

column1: #Text=" You are both lies , and you dare to come before Tario , last and mightiest of the jeddaks of Barsoom , and assert your reality .
#Text=" And leave the Princess of Ptarth here alone ? " cried Carthoris .
#Text=Jav brushed closely past him , whispering :
#Text=" Follow me -- he cannot harm her , except to kill ; and that he can do whether you remain or not .

#Text= If I may not kill thin air , " he asked , " how , then , shall I fear that thin air may kill me ? "

column1: #Text=" You saw the Torquasians fall before the bowmen ? " asked Jav .
#Text=Carthoris nodded .
#Text=" So would you fall before them , and without one single chance for self-defence or revenge . "
#Text=As they talked Jav led Carthoris to a small room in one of the numerous towers of the palace .
#Text=Here were couches , and Jav bid the Heliumite be seated .
#Text=For several minutes the Lotharian eyed his prisoner , for such Carthoris now realized himself to be .
#Text=" I am half convinced that you are real , " he said at last .
#Text=Carthoris laughed .
#Text=" Of course I am real , " he said .
#Text=" What caused you to doubt it ?

column3:
_	_	_	_

#Text= So may I see and feel the bowmen , " replied Jav , " and yet we all know that they , at least , are not real . "

column1: #Text=Carthoris showed by the expression of his face his puzzlement at each new reference to the mysterious bowmen -- the vanishing soldiery of Lothar .
#Text=" What , then , may they be ? " he asked .
#Text=" You really do not know ? " asked Jav .
#Text=Carthoris shook his head negatively .
#Text=" I can almost believe that you have told us the truth and that you are really from another part of Barsoom , or from another world .
